# DDD Domain Language

## Ubiquitous Language

Use these terms consistently in class names, methods, variables, tests, and commits:

| Term | Use | Avoid |
|------|-----|-------|
| Project | Editing workspace | Session, Document, Workspace |
| Media | Uploaded asset in library | File, Asset, Blob |
| Clip | Timeline segment | Segment, Entry, Block |
| Render | Final video output | Export, Process, Encode |
| Preview | Short low-quality render | Thumbnail video, Sample |
| Timeline | Ordered tracks of clips | Sequence, Playlist |

## Package Boundaries

| Package | Contains |
|---------|----------|
| `project/` | Domain entities, value objects, domain services |
| `service/` | Application services (use-case orchestration) |
| `model/` | Legacy API DTOs — do not add new domain concepts here |
| `infra/` | Persistence adapters, serializers, exception mappers |

New domain types belong in `project/`, not `model/`.

## Aggregate: Project

`Project` is the aggregate root. Mutations go through it:

```java
// ❌ BAD — anemic, logic in controller
project.getMedias().add(media);
projects.update(project);

// ✅ GOOD — behavior on aggregate
project.attachMedia(media);
projectRepository.save(project);
```

## Value Objects

`ScreenSize`, `FrameRate`, `MediaType` are value objects — immutable, compared by value, no identity field.

## Repository Language

```java
// ✅ Domain-facing names
Project findById(ProjectId id);
void save(Project project);
List<Project> findAll();

// ❌ Infrastructure leaking
MongoCollection<Project> collection();
```

## Anti-Patterns

- **Anemic domain** — entities with only getters/setters and all logic in services.
- **DTO duplication** — `TimelineProject` and `Project` describing the same concept; consolidate instead of syncing.
- **Primitive obsession** — raw `String id` instead of typed `ProjectId` / `MediaId` for new code.
- **Infrastructure in domain** — `@BsonId`, `@Inject`, `MongoClient` in domain classes (tolerate existing annotations; do not add more).
